                <h2 class="subheading">Introduction</h2>
                <p>@Html.Raw(@Model.BlogSummary.Replace("\n", "<br>"))</p> 
                <p>Unveiled as a near-production concept, the Harrier EV is Tata’s attempt to deliver a feature-rich, high-range electric SUV that rivals both international and domestic offerings. In this article, we explore the <span class="font-weight-700">launch details, pricing, features, battery specs, and more.</span></p>
                <div class="div-line"></div>
                <h3 class="subheading">Tata Harrier EV: Expected Launch Timeline</h3>
                <div class="row m-b20">
                    <div class="col-lg-12 col-md-12 text-center image-height"><img src="~/images/blogs/2025/june/tataevharrier/front.webp" alt="bikecarhubsidetataevharrierfront" title="bikecarhubsidetataevharrierfront" /></div>
                </div>
                <p>The Tata Harrier EV was officially showcased at <span class="font-weight-700">Auto Expo 2023, </span>drawing significant attention. Tata has confirmed that the Harrier EV is in the final stages of development, with a <span class="font-weight-700">launched on 3rd June, 2025.</span></p>
                <p>Production is likely to begin by the end of 2024, with test mules already spotted on Indian roads. Pre-launch teasers and variant announcements are expected in Q4 2024.</p>
                <div class="div-line"></div>
                <h3 class="subheading">Expected Price in India</h3>
                <p>While Tata hasn't officially revealed the pricing, the Harrier EV is expected to start around <span class="font-weight-700">₹28 lakh to ₹35 lakh (ex-showroom), </span>depending on the variant and battery pack.</p>
                <p>This price puts it right in the middle of the premium EV SUV market—<span class="font-weight-700">more expensive than the Nexon EV </span>but competitively priced against global models like the <span class="font-weight-700">MG ZS EV, BYD Atto 3,</span> and the upcoming <span class="font-weight-700">Mahindra XUV.e8.</span></p>
                <div class="div-line"></div>
                <h3 class="subheading">Design & Styling Enhancements</h3>
                <div class="row m-b20">
                    <div class="col-lg-12 col-md-12 text-center image-height"><img src="~/images/blogs/2025/june/tataevharrier/side.webp" alt="bikecarhubsidetataevharrierside" title="bikecarhubsidetataevharrierside" /></div>
                </div>
                <p>The Harrier EV retains the muscular stance of the regular Harrier but adds distinctive EV styling elements:</p>
                <ul>
                    <li><span class="font-weight-700">Closed-off front grille </span>with a futuristic textured pattern</li>
                    <li><span class="font-weight-700">Connected LED DRLs</span> and sharp LED headlamps</li>
                    <li><span class="font-weight-700">Aero-optimized alloy wheels</span> for better efficiency</li>
                    <li><span class="font-weight-700">Sleek EV-specific badging</span></li>
                    <li><span class="font-weight-700">Updated bumper and rear lighting</span> inspired by the Harrier facelift</li>
                </ul>
                <p>Overall, the Harrier EV carries a clean and premium design that blends familiarity with futuristic cues.</p>
                <div class="div-line"></div>
                <h3 class="subheading">Battery, Range & Charging</h3>
                <div class="row m-b20">
                    <div class="col-lg-12 col-md-12 text-center image-height"><img src="~/images/blogs/2025/june/tataevharrier/rear.webp" alt="bikecarhubsidetataevharrierrear" title="bikecarhubsidetataevharrierrear" /></div>
                </div>
                <p>While official specs are still under wraps, here's what’s expected:</p>
