                    <li><span class="font-weight-700">Battery Pack:</span> 75 kWh Lithium-ion</li>
                    <li><span class="font-weight-700">Expected Range: </span>622 km</li>
                    <li><span class="font-weight-700">Charging:</span>
                        <ul>
                            <li><span class="font-weight-700">AC Charging:</span> 7.2 kW onboard charger</li>
                            <li><span class="font-weight-700">DC Fast Charging:</span> 125 kW CCS2 compatibility</li>
                            <li><span class="font-weight-700">0–80% </span>in around <span class="font-weight-700">25 minutes </span>using fast charger</li>
                </ul>
                </ul>
                <p>Tata is expected to use<span class="font-weight-700"> Ziptron Gen-2 EV architecture, </span>improving energy density, efficiency, and charging times.</p>
                <div class="div-line"></div>
                <h3 class="subheading">Motor & Performance</h3>
                <p>The Harrier EV will likely offer <span class="font-weight-700">both FWD (single motor) </span>and <span class="font-weight-700">AWD (dual motor) </span>configurations. While exact output figures are not revealed, estimates point toward:</p>
                <ul>
                    <li><span class="font-weight-700">Power Output: </span> 390 bhp</li>
                    <li><span class="font-weight-700">Torque: </span>Over 504 Nm</li>
                    <li><span class="font-weight-700">Drive Modes: </span> Eco, City, Sport</li>
                    <li><span class="font-weight-700">Regenerative Braking: </span> Multiple levels</li>
                    <li><span class="font-weight-700">Acceleration (0–100 km/h): </span> Expected around 6.3 seconds (AWD) </li>
                </ul>
                <p>This will position the Harrier EV as one of the sportier EV SUVs in its price segment.</p>
                <div class="div-line"></div>
                <h3 class="subheading">Features & Technology</h3>
                <p>Tata Motors is known for offering <span class="font-weight-700">feature-loaded cabins, </span>and the Harrier EV is no exception. Expected features include:</p>
                <ul>
                    <li><span class="font-weight-700">12.3-inch infotainment touchscreen </span>with new UI</li>
                    <li><span class="font-weight-700">10.25-inch digital driver display</span></li>
                    <li><span class="font-weight-700">Panoramic sunroof with ambient lighting</span></li>
                    <li><span class="font-weight-700">Connected car tech with Tata iRA 2.0</span></li>
                    <li><span class="font-weight-700">Over-the-air (OTA) software updates</span></li>
